Promised Land, Sugaree, Cassidy, Candyman, The Music Never Stopped, It Must Have Been The Roses, Looks Like Rain, Tennessee Jed, Let It Grow-> Might As Well
Set II
Saint Stephen-> Not Fade Away-> Drums-> Stella Blue, Samson & Delilah, Friend Of The Devil, Dancin' In The Streets-> The Wheel-> Sugar Magnolia-> Scarlet Begonias-> Sunshine Daydream, E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text: lifelong fav thank you. wore the wheels off this one long ago. superb quality. st.->nfa->st.->stella. is so deep. Stella appears like dawn. thank you Betty etc.

Crisp! Back in the early 90s when I collected GD tapes, my buddy and I had the first set of this show; it was our first "Betty Board" and we couldn't believe how good it sounded when compared to some of our other shows.
Hearing it today for the first time in a long while brings back some good memories and it still sounds awesome, as does the show before this one.
Thank you Betty Cantor!
